# .dockerignore for the tfd (Treatfighter GSP) image build context.
#
# The Dockerfile ships the context with `COPY . .`, then runs
# `make distclean || true` and `./autogen.sh && ./configure && make`, which
# regenerates every autotools / libtool / protobuf artifact from scratch.  So
# dropping generated files, VCS metadata, secrets and logs here can only shrink
# the context -- it never changes the build output.  Everything the build needs
# is deliberately KEPT: src/ proto/ proto2/ database/ contrib/ docs/, the *.am
# templates, configure.ac, autogen.sh, config.{guess,sub}, config.h.in, and the
# GNU-automake-required README / NEWS / AUTHORS / ChangeLog / COPYING.
#
# NOTE: build artifacts live in subdirectories (src/, database/, ...), so their
# patterns need a leading `**/` -- a bare `*.o` would only match the root.

# Version-control metadata (a git-worktree pointer file here) and repo config.
.git
.gitignore

# Secrets -- never ship RPC / private keys into the build context.
.env
.env.*
*.key
*.pem

# Agentic-workflow session scratch (task briefs / reports).
.superpowers

# Logs -- config.log, */test-suite.log, ... are regenerated inside the
# container by `make` / `make check`.
**/*.log

# Python bytecode caches.
**/__pycache__
**/*.pyc

# Autotools generated output + cache (rebuilt by autogen.sh / configure).
autom4te.cache
config.status
**/Makefile

# Libtool / compiler build artifacts (rebuilt by make).
**/.deps
**/.libs
**/*.o
**/*.lo
**/*.la

# Built binaries (rebuilt by make; `make distclean` removes them too).
/src/tfd
/src/tests
/src/goldenreplay_tests
/src/loadbench_tests
/src/reorg_tests
/src/reorg_game_tests

# JS deps (not part of the C++ build; only present if a tool dropped them).
**/node_modules
